Piezoelectricity describes the reversible interaction between electrical and mechanical states in specific materials. It refers to the development of electric potential across output terminals under applied mechanical stress [98]. The inverse piezoelectric effect is the indication of mechanical strain due to the applied electric field. Based on the working principle, PENGs can be categorized into three types: (1) the d33\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
